OL,3,CFarming subsidy: Welsh Government
OL,4,Cbraced for reaction to revised scheme
OL,6,F"We've listened, and we'll continue to
OL,7,Flisten. It's clear that the people of
OL,8,FWales want us to back Welsh farming,
OL,9,Fbut they also want to see nature
OL,10,Frestored, soils protected, water
OL,11,Fquality in our rivers improved, access
OL,12,Fto the countryside maintained and
OL,13,Fnature supported to recover and
OL,14,Fthrive."
OL,16,FBut the National Farmers Union in
OL,17,FWales says that the scheme must work
OL,18,Ffor every farm in Wales. Aled Jones,
OL,19,FPresident of NFU Cymru, says that
OL,20,Fagriculture is the bedrock for Wales'
OL,21,Ffood and drinks sector.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
